[root@srm ~]# rpm -qf /etc/bestman2/conf/bestman2.rc
bestman2-client-2.3.0-20.osg32.el6.noarch
bestman2-tester-2.3.0-20.osg32.el6.noarch
bestman2-server-2.3.0-20.osg32.el6.noarch

As you can see, the repo is osg vs osg32, too and one is el5 and the
other is el6.
So, there is more than version difference.
Since the one with 2.3.0-20.osg32.el6 is the production SE, I am using a
hack with a wrapper script that avoids the collision
between -v and -i option.
I am not sure if this is enough info for you to check further.
Thanks,
Bockjoo

