<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; [Duplicate message snipped]</font></pre></div><div class='update_description'><i onclick="document.location='22741#1413580498'; reset_anchor();" class="pull-right icon icon-share"></i><div class="header"><time datetime="2014-10-17T21:14:58+00:00">Oct 17, 2014 09:14 PM UTC</time> by <b>Carl Edquist</b><a class="anchor" name="1413580498">&nbsp;</a></div><pre>Hi Bockjoo,

In /etc/sudoers, is the &#34;requiretty&#34; line commented out, like this?

#Defaults    requiretty

If not you may need to otherwise sudo will not accept a password from stdin from bestman2.  (It will require it to be typed on a tty.)

There is some more bestman2 specific stuff you need to make sure is added to /etc/sudoers also, which is documented here&#58;

<a href='https&#58;//twiki.opensciencegrid.org/bin/view/Documentation/Release3/InstallOSGBestmanSE#4_4_Modify_etc_sudoers' target='_blank' rel='nofollow'>https&#58;//twiki.opensciencegrid.org/bin/view/Documentation/Release3/InstallOSGBestmanSE#4_4_Modify_etc_sudoers</a>

Can you make sure all that is set up in /etc/sudoers first, and then see if it works for you?

Thanks!
Carl</pre></div><div class='update_description'><i onclick="document.location='22741#1413569248'; reset_anchor();" class="pull-right icon icon-share"></i><div class="header"><time datetime="2014-10-17T18:07:28+00:00">Oct 17, 2014 06:07 PM UTC</time> by <b>Suchandra Thapa</b><a class="anchor" name="1413569248">&nbsp;</a></div><pre>Hi Bockjoo, I added Carl to this ticket.  He should be able to help out here.

Suchandra</pre></div><div class='update_description'><i onclick="document.location='22741#1413397367'; reset_anchor();" class="pull-right icon icon-share"></i><div class="header"><time datetime="2014-10-15T18:22:47+00:00">Oct 15, 2014 06:22 PM UTC</time> by <b>Kyle Gross</b><a class="anchor" name="1413397367">&nbsp;</a></div><pre>From&#58; Bockjoo Kim &#60;bockjoo@....&#62;
To&#58; osg-storage@...., goc@....
Subject&#58; Why sudoCommand=sudo -i does not work anymore?
Date-Sent&#58; Tuesday, October 14, 2014 8&#58;16 PM -0400

Hi,
Until sometime ago, in the bestman2.rc,
sudoCommand=sudo -i
worked.
But this does not work anymore because bestman2 is trying so hard
to validate the sudo command with &#39;sudo -v -S&#39;.
If I configure the bestman2.rc with sudoCommand=sudo -i,
sudo -i -v -S does not work
so bestman thinks it failed the validation.
This works with
bestman2-tester-2.3.0-16.osg.el5
but not with bestman2-server-2.3.0-20.osg32.el6.noarch

I need the option sudo option &#39;-i&#39; to preserve the umask of the mapped users.
Is there a way to avoid the sudo validation &#39;sudo -v -S&#39; via xml or some
configuration?
Otherwise, please go back and support the manual entry for the sudoCommand=sudo -i!
Thanks,
Bockjoo</pre></div><div class='update_description'><i onclick="document.location='22741#1413337001'; reset_anchor();" class="pull-right icon icon-share"></i><div class="header"><time datetime="2014-10-15T01:36:41+00:00">Oct 15, 2014 01:36 AM UTC</time> by <b>Ricky Pirtle</b><a class="anchor" name="1413337001">&nbsp;</a></div><pre>From&#58; Bockjoo Kim &#60;bockjoo@....&#62;
